feat(task-16): dedicated stock adjustment modal with delta + notes

Adds a focused "Adjust Stock" workflow so staff can correct inventory
discrepancies with a signed delta and an optional reason note, rather
than having to use the full product edit form.

## Backend (routes/api.py)
- New POST /api/products/<id>/adjust-stock endpoint (JSON body)
- Accepts `delta` (signed int, required, non-zero) and `notes` (optional string)
- Applies delta to product.quantity atomically
- Writes InventoryLog(reason="manual", delta=delta, notes=notes) — the
  notes field added in Task #15 is now actually populated
- Returns updated quantity in response for client-side confirmation

## Frontend
- New "Adjust Stock" modal (max-width 440px) between Stock History and
  Product modals in inventory.html
- Shows current stock count prominently in a read-only summary row
- Delta input with live preview: "New stock will be 12 (+5)" color-coded
  green for additions, red for removals
- Optional Reason/Notes textarea with placeholder examples
- Client-side validation: blocks zero delta with inline error message
- Submit button shows "Saving…" + disabled state during request
- On success: modal closes, product table reloads immediately
- New sliders icon button (fa-sliders) added to each product row between
  Edit and History buttons

## No schema changes — InventoryLog.notes column already exists from Task #15
